Cody hesitated, eyeing the opening next to the staircase. "It's not the way we came, Lulu," he said, "but worth the chance, I think. Anything to get us out of here more quickly." He moved into the passageway, no longer running but still moving faster than he had been before the shop. After a bit of blessedly uneventful exploration, he found the way forward blocked by a large boulder. "Never mind that, Lulu," he said. "If my mental map is correct, we should head to the right anyway." Lulu yipped and dashed off, surprisingly in the direction indicated.
